<p>I have a contenteditable div like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div contenteditable="true" ng-model="name"&gt;{{ name }}&lt;/div&gt; &lt;input type="button" ng-click="checkScope()" value="Click me"&gt; </code></pre>  <p>In my controller:</p>  <pre><code>var app = angular.module('sbAdminApp', []); app.controller('MyCtrl', function($scope) {     $scope.name = 'Adrian';      $scope.checkScope = function(){         console.log($scope.name);     } }); </code></pre>  <p>How can I get the latest value of contenteditable div using scope when I click the button?</p>